news.title: Raze all bungalows in Alibaug violating CRZ norms: Activists
news.para: The activists added that since law for CRZ violations is the same for all citizens, uniform action must also take place against all illegal bungalows along this coastal belt so as to safeguard the environment.

news.title: Noida: Forced to rely on temporary power connection, say Hilston Urbtech residents
news.para: According to residents, the builder had taken a temporary connection during construction, but even after families started living in the society, it continued using that.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Panchayat buys land for flats, fund crisis forces plot division
news.para: Kilimanoor panchayat is now deliberating on future course of action as the government has directed the local body to divide the plot purchased for apartment complex among the beneficiaries of the scheme based on priority.

news.title: Buildings with defunct rainwater harvesting systems to invite fines
news.para: As per the norms, rainwater harvesting systems are mandatory for residential and commercial buildings constructed on and above 500 sqm plots.

news.title: Unsold Chandigarh housing board properties to go under the hammer again
news.para: Out of these properties, around 95 are commercial properties belonging to leasehold category, while remaining are residential properties, which are mainly flats, of freehold nature.

news.title: Chennai: 216 flats in Anna Nagar told to raze illegal portions in 180 days
news.para: While approval was for a group development comprising 944 dwelling units spread over 59 blocks in 1994, deviations proliferated in 28 blocks, with constuctions added illegally.

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra slashes home loan rate to 8%
news.para: The Pune-based lender has also slashed interest rate on personal loans to 8.9 per cent from the existing 11.35 per cent effective Monday (October 17, 2022), BoM said in a statement.

news.title: Property registrations in Mumbai continue to scale heights
news.para: Property sales during Navratri - between September 26 and October 4 - recorded a 14% year-on-year growth at 3,659 apartments, against 3,025 homes sold during the previous Navratri period between October 7, 2021, and October 15, 2021, showed the data from the inspector general of registration, Maharashtra.

news.title: Karnataka: Property registrations soar, revenue at all-time high
news.para: ​However, this year's data shows that while nearly nine lakh property registrations were recorded between June and September, revenue of Rs 5,699cr, the highest in recent times, flowed into the exchequer.

news.title: Aviom India Housing Finance to raise $30 million via share sales
news.para: Japan’s Gojo-backed Aviom, with Rs 990 crore in loan assets, is in talks with a global pension fund and a domestic private equity fund for fresh capital infusion, founder-cum-managing director Kajal Ilmi told ET.

news.title: Tardeo towers: FIR against S D Corporation for 'violations'
news.para: The police have registered an FIR based on the directions of the Girgaum magistrate court. Social worker Vaibhav Gawli had filed a private complaint in the court alleging violations.

news.title: Gurugram: As plaster falls off walls, DLF New Town Heights residents seek an audit
news.para: According to residents, the project has several structural deficiencies, including chunks of plaster and concrete falling off frequently, cracks in balconies and leakage in shafts, which pose threats to their safety.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Property tax slabs to be amended in panchayats
news.para: A proposal for amendment into existing norms of property tax recovery by panchayats has been put up by panchayat department in state.

news.title: Goa: Bungalow of builder sealed over loan default
news.para: The mamlatdar, on September 22, under the SARFAESI Act, 2002 passed an order directing Moni to vacate the bungalow measuring 7,681sqm, and to hand over possession within 48 hours.

news.title: Vadodara: Three offences lodged against Siddhi Vinayak Developers for cheating buyers
news.para: The fresh offences were registered by the Manjalpur police when three people filed complaints alleging that Patel had taken advances and part payments of properties booked by them, but did not refund the money when he could not conduct work on the sites.
